      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520023.0221.003-01.00.00%2520CEM%2520IIIB%252042%252C5%2520N-LHSR%2520bulk%2520%25E2%2580%259CECOPlanet%25E2%2580%259D%2520EN_%2520signed/scenarios",
      "@type": "ScenarioSet",
      "sectionTitle": "10 DETAILS OF THE UNDERLYING SCENARIOS USED TO CALCULATE THE IMPACTS",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "module": "A1",
          "number": "10.1",
          "title": "A1 - raw material supply",
          "description": "This module takes into account the extraction and processing of all raw materials and energy which occur upstream to the studied manufacturing process.\n\nThe blast furnace slag input has been economically allocated as a co-product of pig iron production."
        },
        {
          "module": "A2",
          "number": "10.2",
          "title": "A2 – transport to the manufacturer",
          "description": "The raw materials are transported to the manufacturing site. The supplier specific distances have been used."
        },
        {
          "module": "A3",
          "number": "10.3",
          "title": "manufacturing",
          "description": "This module takes into account the production process, no assumptions have been made."
        },
        {
          "module": "A4",
          "number": "10.4",
          "title": "A4 – transport to the building site",
          "description": "Fuel type and consumption of vehicle or vehicle type used for transport:\n- Truck 16-32 ton: 0,037 kg diesel / tkm\n- Truck >32 ton: 0,019 kg diesel / tkm\n- Truck 7.5-16 ton: 0,047 kg diesel / tkm\n\nDistance: 100 km, 100 km, 35 km\n\nCapacity utilisation (including empty returns): Default ecoinvent (all)\n\nBulk density of transported products: -\n\nVolume capacity utilisation factor: Default ecoinvent (all)\n\nThe B-PCR provides default transport scenarios for the transport to the building site for cases where specific data on transport are missing. The B-PCR provides scenarios for this life cycle stage. The following transport steps apply:\n\n– 75% directly to the construction site over 100 km with a Lorry 16-32 ton (EURO5) (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')\n\n– 25% to a supplier over 100 km with a >32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry >32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry >32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U'). Afterwards the product is transported from the supplier to the construction site. 90% of the 25% is transported with a Lorry 16-32 ton (EURO5) over a distance of 35km and 10% of the 25% is transported with a Lorry 7.5-16 ton (EURO5) over a distance of 35km. (ecoinvent records: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U', 'Transport, freight, lorry 7.5-16 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 7.5-16 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')"
        },
        {
          "module": "A5",
          "number": "10.5",
          "title": "A5 – installation in the building",
          "description": "Not applicable for this EPD."
        },
        {
          "module": "B",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B – use stage (excluding potential savings)",
          "description": "Not applicable for this EPD."
        },
        {
          "module": "C",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "C: End of life",
          "description": "Not applicable for this EPD."
        },
        {
          "module": "D",
          "number": "10.8",
          "title": "D – Benefits and loads beyond the system boundaries",
          "description": "Not applicable for this EPD."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520023.0221.003-01.00.00%2520CEM%2520IIIB%252042%252C5%2520N-LHSR%2520bulk%2520%25E2%2580%259CECOPlanet%25E2%2580%259D%2520EN_%2520signed/references",
