      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520023.0221.004-01.00.00%2520Holcim%2520CEM%2520VA%2520(S-V)%2520425%2520N-LH%2520HSR%2520bulk%2520%25E2%2580%259CECOPlanet%25E2%2580%259D%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/references",
      "@type": "Bibliography",
      "bibliography": [],
      "additionalInformation": [
        "The blast furnace slag input has been economically allocated as a co-product of pig iron production.",
        "The impact of the siliceous fly ash (a waste from coal-fire electricity production) has been allocated to the previous system.",
        "The B-PCR provides default transport scenarios for the transport to the building site for cases where specific data on transport are missing. The B-PCR provides scenarios for this life cycle stage. The following transport steps apply: – 75% directly to the construction site over 100 km with a Lorry 16-32 ton (EURO5) (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U') – 25% to a supplier over 100 km with a >32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry >32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry >32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U'). Afterwards the product is transported from the supplier to the construction site. 90% of the 25% is transported with a Lorry 16-32 ton (EURO5) over a distance of 35km and 10% of the 25% is transported with a Lorry 7.5-16 ton (EURO5) over a distance of 35km. (ecoinvent records: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U', 'Transport, freight, lorry 7.5-16 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 7.5-16 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')"
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520023.0221.004-01.00.00%2520Holcim%2520CEM%2520VA%2520(S-V)%2520425%2520N-LH%2520HSR%2520bulk%2520%25E2%2580%259CECOPlanet%25E2%2580%259D%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/sections",
      "@type": "EpdSectionSet",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "number": "11.1",
          "title": "Indoor air",
          "content": "SUBSTANCES TO INDOOR AIR, SOIL\n\nAND WATER DURING THE USE\n\nSTAG E\n\nCement is not in direct contact with indoor air. It is the cement-based products (concrete, mortar…) that are potentially in contact\n\nwith indoor air."
        },
        {
          "number": "11.2",
          "title": "Soil and water",
          "content": "Cement is not in direct contact with indoor air. It is the cement-based products (concrete, mortar…) that are potentially in contact\n\nwith indoor air.\n\nCement is not in direct contact withsoil and water. It is the cement-based products (concrete, mortar…) that are potentially in contact\n\nwith soil and water."
        },
        {
          "number": "12",
          "title": "DEMONSTRATION OF VERIFICATION 3|26B-EPDCEMV/A(S-V)42,5 N-LH HSRbulk“ECOPlanet”",
          "content": "Cement is not in direct contact withsoil and water. It is the cement-based products (concrete, mortar…) that are potentially in contact\n\nwith soil and water.\n\nEN 15804+A2serves as the core PCR\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according to standard EN ISO 14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier:[Evert Vermaut, JanOlieslagerslaan 35,1800 Vilvoorde, rsterckx@vincotte.be]"
        },
        {
          "number": "13",
          "title": "lca interpretation",
          "content": "EN 15804+A2serves as the core PCR\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according to standard EN ISO 14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier:[Evert Vermaut, JanOlieslagerslaan 35,1800 Vilvoorde, rsterckx@vincotte.be]\n\nNot provided."
        },
        {
          "number": "16",
          "title": "ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON REVERSIBILITY",
          "content": "Not applicable for this EPD.\n\nREVERSIBILITY\n\nNot applicable for this EPD."
        }
      ]
    },
