        {
          "number": "14",
          "title": "ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON REVERSIBILITY",
          "content": "13 APPLICATION UNIT\n\nPlasterboard can be usedfor: The application unit relates to thedeclaredunit as follows:\n\n– partition walls: plasterboard is installed on both sides\n\nof thesteel or timberframe\n\nm² installed\n\nSystem Layers\n\n– wall lining. plasterboard is installed ononeside of the\n\nplasterboard\n\nsteel or timber frame\n\n1 2 m²\n\nThe application unit can be 1 m² of partition wall or 1 m² of\n\nwall lining.\n\n2 4 m²\n\nPartition wall\n\n6 m²\n\n3\n\nDepending on the technical demands for the system (fire\n\nresistance,sound insulation,structural strength, …)1 to 3\n\n1 m²\n\n1\n\nlayers of plasterboard can be used.\n\nWall lining 2 2 m²\n\n3 3 m²\n\n®\n\nSimplicity of Ease of handling (sizeRobustness ofmaterial (material\n\nDescription Type of fixing Level of reversibility Speed of disassembly Comment\n\ndisassembly and weight) resistance to disassembly)\n\nGyproc®Rf12,5can beScrews Non reversibleconnection –\n\nmounted on:\n\n– steelprofiles\n\n– timber framing\n\n®"
