    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520024.0263.001-01.00.00%2520Fire%2520damper%2520RF-Technologies-EN_signed/sections",
      "@type": "EpdSectionSet",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "number": "11.1",
          "title": "Indoor air",
          "content": "SUBSTANCES TO INDOOR AIR,\n\nSOIL AND WATER DURING THE\n\nUSE STAG E\n\nThere are noemissions to indoor aircaused by the CU-LT 200x100 fire damper with motorised actuator."
        },
        {
          "number": "11.2",
          "title": "Soil and water",
          "content": "There are noemissions to indoor aircaused by the CU-LT 200x100 fire damper with motorised actuator.\n\nNot applicable, as this product is not in contact with (drinking) water, runoff water, seepage water and surface water."
        },
        {
          "number": "12",
          "title": "DEMONSTRATION OF VERIFICATION",
          "content": "10.8 D–benefits and loads beyond the system boundaries\n\nInmodule D, following waste streamsoriginating from the final productare considered after their end-of-wastepoint: the\n\ndifferentmetals(steel,copper and brass,95% recycled). For packagingwaste:wooden packaging (50% recycled),cardboard\n\npackaging (95% recycled),plastic packaging (35%recycled). The EOL waste treatments are accordingto theB-EPD-PCR\n\ndefault scenariosfor the different waste materials.\n\nProduction of secondary low-alloyed steel:3,366 kg\n\nQUANTITATIVE DESCRIPTION OF\n\nTHE LOADS BEYOND THE\n\nTreatment of copper scrap by electrolytic refining: 0,102 kg\n\nSYSTEM BOUNDARIES\n\nProduction of recycled polyethylene granulates:0,019kg\n\nProduction of recycledPETgranulates: 0,001 kg\n\nThe sorting and shredding of woodchips for recycling:0,840 kg\n\nThe sorting of waste paperboard for recycling:0,130 kg\n\nAvoided production of primary steel: 3,366 kg\n\nAvoided production of primarycopper:0,102kg\n\nQUANTITATIVE DESCRIPTION OF\n\nAvoided production of primary polyethylene granulates: 0,019kg\n\nTHE BENEFITS BEYOND THE\n\nSYSTEM BOUNDARIES Avoided production of primary PET granulates: 0,001 kg\n\nAvoided production of primary wood chips for wooden packaging production: 0,840 kg\n\nAvoided production of primary pulp for paper production: 0,130 kg\n\n11 RELEASE OF DANGEROUS\n\nSUBSTANCES TO INDOOR AIR,\n\nSOIL AND WATER DURING THE\n\nUSE STAG E\n\n11.1 Indoor air\n\nThere are noemissions to indoor aircaused by the CU-LT 200x100 fire damper with motorised actuator.\n\n11.2 Soil and wate r\n\nNot applicable, as this product is not in contact with (drinking) water, runoff water, seepage water and surface water.\n\nVERIFICATION\n\nEN 15804+A2servesas the core PCR.\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according to standard EN ISO 14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThirdparty verifier:\n\nBob Roijen\n\nSGS Intron\n\nDr. Nolenslaan 126"
        },
        {
          "number": "14",
          "title": "ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON REVERSIBILITY",
          "content": "13 TECHNICAL INFORMATION FOR\n\nSCENARIO DEVELOPMENT /\n\nAPPLICATION UNIT\n\nThe information in this EPD is given for one specific fire damper with motorised actuator, produced by Rf-Technologies in\n\nits factory at Oosterzele, Belgium.\n\nThe ratio between application unit and reference flow in the EPD equals 1 (same unit in application unit as in EPD).\n\nThe fire dampers are designed and installedwhere air ducts penetrate fire-resistant compartment wallsin order to restore\n\nthe fire resistance grade of the penetrated wall and to prevent smoke propagation.\n\nInstallation can be donein different varieties, in respect with the Declaration of Performance (DoP)of the product:\n\n• Installation in a rigid wall and floor;\n\n• Installation in flexible wall (metal stud gypsum plasterboard wall);\n\n• Installation in flexible wall (metal stud gypsum plasterboard wall), sealing with gypsum;\n\n• Installation in flexible wall (metal stud gypsum plasterboard wall), sealing withmortar;\n\n• Installation in shaft wall, sealing with gypsum;\n\n• Installation in shaft wall, sealing with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n\n• Installation in shaft wall with IFW installation kit and plaster joint filler;\n\n• Installation in flexible and rigid wall, sealing with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n\n• Installation in rigid floor, sealing with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n\n• Installation remote from the wall, sealing and insulation with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n\n• Installation remote from the wall + GEOFLAM plates (threaded rods and U-shaped steel profiles).\n\nFor each scenario, different materials and processes may be necessary in order to install the product.Details on the\n\ninstallation procedures can be found on the website of the producer through the following link:Optimised rectangular fire\n\ndamper up to 120’ (rft.eu)\n\nThe reversibility of the here consideredCU-LT 200x100 fire damper with motorised actuatorstrongly depends on the type of installation(see chapter 13).Considering the rather large variety in\n\napplication, in the following table, a general qualitative description of reversibility is given for all different applications together.\n\nSimplicity of Ease of handling (sizeRobustness of material (material\n\nDescription Type of fixing Level of reversibility Speed of disassembly Comment\n\ndisassembly and weight) resistance to disassembly)\n\nThe fire damperis Different types of fixationDepending on theDepending on the- Speed of – Material easy to– Material with a long lifespan,\n\ninstalled where air ductswith different sealingapplication: application: disassembly varies frommanipulate by hand,disassembly is possible but the\n\npenetrate fire-resistantmaterials – Reversible – Simple–requiresquick to slow dependingone to two workersmaterial should be handled with care in\n\ncompartment walls connections withthe use of specificon element dimensionsrequired dependingorder to prevent damaging it\n\nlight repairablethough commonandtype andnumber of on dimensions– Disassembly is possible but can cause\n\ndamage tools fixations per distance unit damage to the material due to the type\n\n– Reversible – Simple, but of assembly or fixing used\n\nconnections withcollecting the\n\nnon-repairable material is a bit\n\ndamage more intensive\n\n– Non reversible\n\nconnections"
        }
      ]
    },
