        "complete": true,
        "notes": "Table shows additional impact categories beyond EN 15804. All columns (A1-A5, B1-B7, C1-C4, D) and all 6 indicator rows (PM, IRHH, ETF, HTCE, HTnCE, Land Use) are fully captured. Note that the table footer provides abbreviation explanations: HTCE = HUMAN TOXICITY – CANCER EFFECTS; HTNCE = HUMAN TOXICITY – NON CANCER EFFECTS; ETF = ECOTOXICITY – FRESHWATER; PM = PARTICULATE MATTER; IRHH = IONIZING RADIATION – HUMAN HEALTH EFFECTS. Column C4 appears to have zero values but is present in the table."
      }
