    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520025.0297.002-01.00.00%2520Aliplast%2520STAR75%2520LC%2520Kip%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/lca-study",
      "@type": "LcaStudy",
      "sectionTitle": "LCA-STUDY",
      "standardsAndMethodology": "The allocation procedure described by the European standard EN 15804+A2 has been followed.\n\nCut-off criteria described in EN15804+A2 has been followed: 5% of energy and materials by module and 1% of total energy and raw materials.\n\nFollowing EN15804+A2, flows of biogenic carbon have been allocated according to physical properties, because the net sum of biogenic CO2 uptake and release over modules A1-C4 should be zero. Relevant data records have been adjusted accordingly.\n\nCarbon offsetting is not allowed in the EN 15804+A2 and hence not taken into account in the calculations.",
      "lcaSoftwareAndDatabase": "For the calculation of the LCA results, the software program SimaPro 9.5.1 has been used.\n\nDatabased used for modelling include:\n- Ecoinvent 3.9\n- Industry 2.0",
      "systemBoundaries": "System boundaries (parsed from PDF diagram — no AI)\nPage 11\nDeclared modules (☒): A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, C1, C2, C3, C4, D\nNot declared (☐): B1, B2, B3, B4, B5, B6, B7\nBy life-cycle stage:\nProduct stage: A1, A2, A3\nConstruction installation stage: A4, A5\nEnd of life stage: C1, C2, C3, C4\nBeyond the system boundaries: D\n\nModule labels (vertical text):\nA1: Raw materials\nA2: Transport\nA3: Manufacturing\nA4: Transport\nA5: Construction\nB1: Use\nB2: Maintenance\nB3: Repa\nB4: Replacement\nB5: Refurbishment\nB6: Operational energy use\nB7: Operational water use\nC1: construction\nC2: Transport\nC3: Waste processing\nC4: Disposal\nD: Recovery",
      "productionSites": "The data used for the LCA is specific for this product which is manufactured by a single manufacturer in a single production site.",
      "cutOffCriteria": "The following processes are considered below cut-off: \n• Recycling of raw materials packaging.\n• All activities and energy use related to the offices and personnel.\n• Steel cassettes as packaging of one of the raw materials, as these are re-used countless times.\n• Infrastructure & impacts related to the use of the machines at Aliplast's site.\n\nCut-off criteria described in EN15804+A2 has been followed: 5% of energy and materials by module and 1% of total energy and raw materials.",
      "allocation": "Allocation of inputs and outputs has been necessary in the manufacturing stage A3. Allocation has been performed using physical relationship – annual usage vs. annual volume of the specific window system produced.\nThe allocation procedure described by the European standard EN 15804+A2 has been followed.",
      "dataQuality": "Foreground processes include:\n- Raw Materials used, their packaging, transportation mode and related quantities,\n- Energy mix and amount used for production,\n- Types of product packaging and related quantities,\n- Environmental impacts of raw materials for which EPDs were available,\n- All other quantitative information. \n\nGeneric datasets were used for:\n- Extraction and manufacturing of raw materials, packaging,\n- Transportation and treatment of waste from raw material packaging and production,\n- Waste treatment processes,\n- Transport to end-of-life treatment,\n- End-of-life treatment processes and scenarios.\n\n– Declared value is representative of the representative product – Tilled Window System, which is also a worst case (highest impacts) of the product group covered by this EPD.",
      "timeRepresentativeness": "Manufacturer specific data have been collected for the year 2022.",
      "geographicalRepresentativeness": "Aliplast purchases renewable energy mix from their supplier. Renewable energy mix was modelled based on the statistics for Belgium.\nGWP of this mix is 0.049 kg CO2 eq. / kWh.",
      "impactAssessment": "The characterization factors from EC-JRC were applied: EF 3.1. No additional or deviating characterisation factors were used.",
      "additionalParagraphs": [
        "Following processes were excluded for the inventory:\n- Flows related to human activities such as employee transport and administration activity.",
        "Only product packaging contains biogenic carbon. Following EN15804+A2, flows of biogenic carbon have been allocated according to physical properties, because the net sum of biogenic CO2 uptake and release over modules A1-C4 should be zero. Relevant data records have been adjusted accordingly.\n\nBiogenic carbon content (kg C / FU )\nBiogenic carbon content in product (at the gate) 0\nBiogenic carbon content in accompanying packaging (at the gate) 1.71E-01",
        "This EPD covers 3 types of window systems. The differences between these systems are minor - quantities of only some components vary (handles, fittings, one plastic part). Consequently, this EPD is representative of the worst-case scenario."
      ],
      "subsections": [
        {
          "number": "3.1",
          "title": "Date of LCA-study",
          "content": "The LCA study has been performed in October 2024."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.2",
          "title": "Software",
          "content": "For the calculation of the LCA results, the software program SimaPro 9.5.1 has been used."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.3",
          "title": "Information on allocation",
          "content": "Allocation of inputs and outputs has been necessary in the manufacturing stage A3. Allocation has been performed using physical relationship – annual usage vs. annual volume of the specific window system produced.\nThe allocation procedure described by the European standard EN 15804+A2 has been followed."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.4",
          "title": "Information on cut off",
          "content": "The following processes are considered below cut-off: \n• Recycling of raw materials packaging.\n• All activities and energy use related to the offices and personnel.\n• Steel cassettes as packaging of one of the raw materials, as these are re-used countless times.\n• Infrastructure & impacts related to the use of the machines at Aliplast's site.\n\nCut-off criteria described in EN15804+A2 has been followed: 5% of energy and materials by module and 1% of total energy and raw materials."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.5",
          "title": "Information on excluded processes",
          "content": "Following processes were excluded for the inventory:\n- Flows related to human activities such as employee transport and administration activity."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.6",
          "title": "Information on biogenic carbon modelling",
          "content": "Only product packaging contains biogenic carbon. Following EN15804+A2, flows of biogenic carbon have been allocated according to physical properties, because the net sum of biogenic CO2 uptake and release over modules A1-C4 should be zero. Relevant data records have been adjusted accordingly.\n\nBiogenic carbon content (kg C / FU )\nBiogenic carbon content in product (at the gate) 0\nBiogenic carbon content in accompanying packaging (at the gate) 1.71E-01"
        },
        {
          "number": "3.7",
          "title": "Information on carbon off-setting",
          "content": "Carbon offsetting is not allowed in the EN 15804+A2 and hence not taken into account in the calculations."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.8",
          "title": "Additional or deviating characterization factors",
          "content": "The characterization factors from EC-JRC were applied: EF 3.1. No additional or deviating characterisation factors were used."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.9",
          "title": "Description of the variability",
          "content": "This EPD covers 3 types of window systems. The differences between these systems are minor - quantities of only some components vary (handles, fittings, one plastic part). Consequently, this EPD is representative of the worst-case scenario."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.10",
          "title": "Specificity",
          "content": "The data used for the LCA is specific for this product which is manufactured by a single manufacturer in a single production site."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.11",
          "title": "Period of data collection",
          "content": "Manufacturer specific data have been collected for the year 2022."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.12",
          "title": "Information on data collection",
          "content": "Foreground processes include:\n- Raw Materials used, their packaging, transportation mode and related quantities,\n- Energy mix and amount used for production,\n- Types of product packaging and related quantities,\n- Environmental impacts of raw materials for which EPDs were available,\n- All other quantitative information. \n\nGeneric datasets were used for:\n- Extraction and manufacturing of raw materials, packaging,\n- Transportation and treatment of waste from raw material packaging and production,\n- Waste treatment processes,\n- Transport to end-of-life treatment,\n- End-of-life treatment processes and scenarios.\n\n– Declared value is representative of the representative product – Tilled Window System, which is also a worst case (highest impacts) of the product group covered by this EPD."
        },
        {
          "number": "3.13",
          "title": "Database used for background data",
          "content": "Databased used for modelling include:\n- Ecoinvent 3.9\n- Industry 2.0"
        },
        {
          "number": "3.14",
          "title": "Energy mix",
          "content": "Aliplast purchases renewable energy mix from their supplier. Renewable energy mix was modelled based on the statistics for Belgium.\nGWP of this mix is 0.049 kg CO2 eq. / kWh."
        }
      ]
    },
