    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%252023.0191.006_01.00.01%2520EN%2520Kingspan%2520Kooltherm%2520K12%2520-%2520signed/scenarios",
      "@type": "ScenarioSet",
      "sectionTitle": "10 DETAILS OF THE UNDERLYING SCENARIOS USED TO CALCULATE THE IMPACTS",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "module": "A1",
          "number": "10.1",
          "title": "A1 - raw material supply",
          "description": "This module takes into account the extraction and processing of all raw materials and energy which occur upstream to the studied manufacturing process."
        },
        {
          "module": "A2",
          "number": "10.2",
          "title": "A2 – transport to the manufacturer",
          "description": "The raw materials are transported to the manufacturing site."
        },
        {
          "module": "A3",
          "number": "10.3",
          "title": "manufacturing",
          "description": "This module takes into account the production process."
        },
        {
          "module": "A4",
          "number": "10.4",
          "title": "A4 – transport to the building site",
          "description": "Fuel type and consumption of vehicle or vehicle type used for transport: Truck 16-32 ton, 0,256 l diesel / km\nDistance: 180 km\nCapacity utilisation (including empty returns): 50%\nBulk density of transported products: Ecoinvent\nVolume capacity utilisation factor: Ecoinvent\n\nKooltherm® K12 is only sold on a project basis. Kooltherm will therefore only be delivered directly to construction sites.\n\nThe following transport scenario applies:\n– 100% directly to the construction site over 180 km with a 16-32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')"
        },
        {
          "module": "A5",
          "number": "10.5",
          "title": "A5 – installation in the building",
          "description": "At the construction site, packaging materials are released. Also 2% material losses have been taken into account\n\nParts of the installation quantity:\nMaterial losses: 0,056 kg Kooltherm K12 - THE QUANTITY OF MATERIAL LOST DUE TO CUTTING IT IN THE RIGHT SHAPE\nPackaging: 0,0135 kg PE foil, 0,0504 kg EPS Skids - THE PACKAGING WASTE AT THE CONSTRUCTION SITE"
        },
        {
          "module": "C",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "C: End of life",
          "description": "The default scenario for synthetic isolation materials in the NBN/DTD B08-001 states 5% of the waste treatment consists of landfilling, the other 95% consists of incineration and/or energetic valorisation.\n\nAfter incineration the aluminium will be recycled from the bottom ash (based on sustainability report of Indaver: samen werken aan een circulaire economie, duurzaamheidsrapport 2021).\n\nThe default scenario for metals (non-ferro) in the NBN/DTD B08-001 states 5% of the waste treatment consists of landfilling, the other 95% consists of recycling.\n\nModule C2 – Transport to waste processing:\nTruck 16-32 ton, 0,256 l diesel/km, 30 km, 50% capacity utilisation, Ecoinvent scenario density and assumptions\nTruck 16-32 ton, 0,256 l diesel/km, 50 km, 50% capacity utilisation, Ecoinvent scenario density and assumptions\nTruck 16-32 ton, 0,256 l diesel/km, 10 km, 50% capacity utilisation, Ecoinvent scenario density and assumptions\n\nEnd-of-life modules – C3 and C4:\nWastes collected separately: 0 kg\nWastes collected as mixed construction waste: 2,80 kg\nWaste for re-use: 0 kg\nWaste for recycling: 0,09 kg\nWaste for energy recovery: 2,57 kg\nWaste for final disposal: 0,14 kg"
        },
        {
          "module": "D",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "D – Benefits and loads beyond the system boundaries",
          "description": "QUANTITATIVE DESCRIPTION OF THE LOADS BEYOND THE SYSTEM BOUNDARIES: No loads\n\nQUANTITATIVE DESCRIPTION OF THE BENEFITS BEYOND THE SYSTEM BOUNDARIES:\nAvoided production of 13,4 MJ of heat using natural gas\nAvoided production of 6,7 MJ of Belgian electricity mix"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%252023.0191.006_01.00.01%2520EN%2520Kingspan%2520Kooltherm%2520K12%2520-%2520signed/sections",
      "@type": "EpdSectionSet",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "number": "11.1",
          "title": "Indoor air",
          "content": "The product is not intended for indoor use and hence no specific VOC emission tests are performed."
        },
        {
          "number": "11.2",
          "title": "Soil and water",
          "content": "The product is not intended for indoor use and hence no specific VOC emission tests are performed.\n\nTheproduct does not come in contact with soil or water."
        },
        {
          "number": "12",
          "title": "DEMONSTRATION OF VERIFICATION",
          "content": "11 RELEASE OF DANGEROUS\n\nSUBSTANCES TO INDOOR AIR,\n\nSOIL AND WATER DURING THE\n\nUSE STAG E\n\n11.1 Indoor air\n\nThe product is not intended for indoor use and hence no specific VOC emission tests are performed.\n\n11.2 Soil and wate r\n\nTheproduct does not come in contact with soil or water.\n\nVERIFICATION\n\nEN 15804+A2serves as the core PCR\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according to standard EN ISO14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier:\n\nVinçotte nv\n\nRamses Sterckx\n\nJan Olieslagerslaan 35 1800 Vilvoorde\n\nrsterckx@vincotte.b"
        },
        {
          "number": "13",
          "title": "lca interpretation",
          "content": "12 DEMONSTRATION OF\n\nVERIFICATION\n\nEN 15804+A2serves as the core PCR\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according to standard EN ISO14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier:\n\nVinçotte nv\n\nRamses Sterckx\n\nJan Olieslagerslaan 35 1800 Vilvoorde\n\nrsterckx@vincotte.b\n\nAll impact categories are mainlydetermined by the raw materials supply in A1. For GWP(and to less extend also the values\n\nfor ODP, FAETP and MAETP) also the incinerationemissions at the end of life have a significant environmental impact. The\n\npotential creditsfor thermal and electricalenergy are declared in module D and result in negative valuesfor most of the\n\nimpact categories."
        }
      ]
    },
