    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FBEPD_024.0156.002-01.00.00_Derbigum%2520NT%25204-%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/scenarios",
      "@type": "ScenarioSet",
      "sectionTitle": "10 DETAILS OF THE UNDERLYING SCENARIOS USED TO CALCULATE THE IMPACTS",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "module": "A1",
          "number": "10.1",
          "title": "A1 – raw material supply",
          "description": "Module A1 comprises impacts from extraction and processing of raw materials including bitumen, polymers, reinforcements (glass- and polyester fibre), fillers, etc. The recycling process of secondary raw materials used in the product is also included in module A1."
        },
        {
          "module": "A2",
          "number": "10.2",
          "title": "A2 – transport to the manufacturer",
          "description": "The raw materials are transported to the manufacturing site. Primary data are provided by Derbigum."
        },
        {
          "module": "A3",
          "number": "10.3",
          "title": "A3 – manufacturing",
          "description": "Module A3 includes the manufacturing of the final product, production and transport of larger packaging materials (pallets), combustion of fuels on site (natural gas, diesel, and propane), as well as end-of-life treatment of waste generated during manufacturing. It also includes the production of electricity (Derbigum mix)."
        },
        {
          "module": "A4",
          "number": "10.4",
          "title": "A4 – transport to the building site",
          "description": "Fuel type and consumption of vehicle or vehicle type used for transport: Truck 16-32 ton, 0,256 l diesel / km\nDistance: 100 km and 100 km+ 35 km\nCapacity utilisation (including empty returns): Default ecoinvent\nBulk density of transported products: Default ecoinvent\nVolume capacity utilisation factor: Default ecoinvent\n\nDefault B-PCR distances for delivery are used, completed with specific data provided by Derbigum for the repartition of the transport. The following transport steps apply:\n– 20% directly to the construction site over 100 km with a 16-32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')\n– 80% to a supplier over 100 km with a 16 -32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')\n– 100% of these 80% is transported over 35 km from supplier to construction site with a 16-32 ton lorry (ecoinvent record: 'Transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 {RER}| transport, freight, lorry 16-32 metric ton, EURO5 | Cut-off, U')"
        },
        {
          "module": "A5",
          "number": "10.5",
          "title": "A5 – installation in the building",
          "description": "The product can be used on different types of substrates: wood, concrete, and sheet steel. It can also be installed on a vapour- barrier layer such as Derbicoat NT 2.5 (see B-EPD 24.0156.01- 01.00.00) to form a double-layer roof waterproofing coating solution.\n\nThe installation includes an overlap of the layers (10.5%) for complete waterproofing. It is integrated in the in the FU (in modules A1, A2, A3, and A4) of the present B-EPD.\n\nThe installation mode is \"fully torched by use of flame\" (torched with flame). The production and combustion of propane for torching are counted (+ associated CO2 emissions). The amount of propane for 1 m² is 0,150 kg/m² (= kg/FU) (prEN 17388 by use of flame:2022).\n\nWaste from the installation (trimming waste, 2%) is classified as material for recycling (95%)- and waste for landfill (5%). This waste is measured for 1 m² \"net installed\" (0,02 m²/FU).\n\nAt the construction site, packaging materials are released. The impacts from waste management processes are included in module A5, whereas potential benefits from material reuse/recycling and energy recovery from incineration are reported in module D.\n\nParts of the installation:\n- Processes necessary for the installation of the product: Manual installation\n- Fixation materials: 0,150 kg/FU Propane for torching\n- Jointing materials: -\n- Treatments: -\n- Material losses: 9,006 E-02 kg/FU Trimming waste (2%) (0,02 m²/FU)\n- Packaging: 0,1406 kg/FU Pallet waste (including installation waste and overlap)\n- Others: 10,5% Additional sheet for overlap on the layers for complete waterproofing (already included the FU)\n- Ancillary materials for installation (specified by material): Insert information\n- Water use: -\n- Other resource use: Propane 0,150 kg/FU\n- Quantitative description of energy type (regional mix) and consumption during the installation process: -\n- Waste materials on the building site before waste processing, generated by the product's installation (specified by type): Trimming waste 9,006 E-02 kg/FU 2% (0,02 m²/FU); Packaging waste: pallet 0,1406 kg/FU\n- Output materials (specified by type) as result of waste processing at the building site e.g. of collection for recycling, for energy recovery, disposal (specified by route): Trimming waste 9,006 E-02 kg/FU 95% recycled by Derbigum, 5% \"non sorted waste: landfill\"\n- Direct emissions to ambient air, soil and water: None\n- Distance: Derbigum recycling facility 128 km* 8,555 E-2 kg/FU; Sorting centre 30 km 4,503 E-03 kg/FU** 1,406 kg/FU***; Landfill 50 km 4,503 E-03 kg/FU**; Incineration 100 km 5,625 E-02 kg/FU***\n* Corresponding to the average A4 transport distance\n** 5% installation waste\n*** Pallet waste"
        },
        {
          "module": "B1",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B1 – Use",
          "description": "No information could be collected on the emissions of the products to air or water during their use."
        },
        {
          "module": "B2",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B2 – Maintenance",
          "description": "No product maintenance takes place during the reference service life."
        },
        {
          "module": "B3",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B3 - Repair",
          "description": "No product repair takes place during the reference service life. Planned replacement is accounted in module B4."
        },
        {
          "module": "B4",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B4 – Replacement",
          "description": "The Derbigum NT 4 has to be replaced after 40 years to ensure a correct waterproofing. In practice, the existing layer is left in place and an additional layer of Derbigum NT 4 is added.\n\nThe inventory included the amount of Derbigum NT 4 for 1 m² including overlap (10,5%), the installation losses (2%), and the propane for fully torched installation on the existing layer.\n\nThe waste includes the installation losses and the packaging waste.\n\nThe scenario is identical to the installation A5:\nMaterials:\n− Derbigum NT 4: production and transport of 1 m² + overlapping 10,5%, + 2% losses [A1,A2,A3,A4]\nInstallation:\n− Ancillary material: 0,150 kg propane/m² + associated CO2 emissions\n− Derbigum NT 4 waste: 95% of the installation losses are recycled as Gumix APP and 5% are landfilled\n− Pallet waste: the BE-PCR scenario for pallet end of life is respected\n− Transport of the waste: as in A5\n\nThe impacts from waste management processes are included in module B4, whereas potential benefits from material reuse/recycling and energy recovery from incineration are reported in module D."
        },
        {
          "module": "B5",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B5 - Refurbishment",
          "description": "No product refurbishment takes place during the reference service life."
        },
        {
          "module": "B6",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B6 – Operational energy use",
          "description": "The product does not use energy during its use."
        },
        {
          "module": "B7",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B7 – Operational water use",
          "description": "The product does not use water during its use."
        },
        {
          "module": "C1",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "C1: Deconstruction",
          "description": "The waterproofing layer is removed manually, and no impacts are readily attributed to the product whereby no emissions arise from the deconstruction"
        },
        {
          "module": "C2",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "C2: Transport",
          "description": "Comprises impacts from transportation of the deconstructed products after 60 years to the waste processing (sorting centre and landfill, or recycling site).\n\nThe amount of material to consider includes the overlap, and the second layer added as replacement in module B4 (and its overlap). It corresponds to 2 x 1 FU.\n\nModule C2 – Transport to waste processing:\n- Type of vehicle: Lorry 16-32 t EURO5\n- Fuel consumption: EI (ecoinvent default value)\n- Distance to Derbigum facility: 128 km\n- Distance to Sorting centre: 30 km\n- Distance to Landfill: 50 km\n- Capacity utilisation: EI\n- Density of products: 1126 kg / m3"
        },
        {
          "module": "C3",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "C3: Waste processing",
          "description": "Derbigum roofs sold in Belgian (or foreign) market come with a \"take back\" guarantee, which means all losses during installation are collected and transported back to Derbigum recycling facility in Belgium. It is assumed that 95% of the Derbigum NT 4 waste are recovered and recycled.\n\nThe burden for recycling process and the benefits from replacing bitumen are recorded in Module D.\n\nThe remaining 5% are considered to be mixed with the other \"non sorted\" waste of the deconstruction site. They go to the sorting centre where they are handled or moved once. Default values for BE-PCR are applied.\n\nEnd-of-life modules – C3 and C4:\n- Wastes collected separately: 9,454 kg/FU\n- Wastes collected as mixed construction waste: 0,4976 kg/FU\n- Waste for re-use: -\n- Waste for recycling: 9,454 kg/FU\n- Waste for energy recovery: -\n- Waste for final disposal: 0,4976 kg/FU"
        },
        {
          "module": "C4",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "C4: Disposal",
          "description": "The residual 5% of membrane waste are landfilled in this module."
        },
        {
          "module": "D",
          "number": "10.8",
          "title": "D – Benefits and loads beyond the system boundaries",
          "description": "Module D is calculated in accordance with EN 15804:2012+A2:2019 and BE-PCR. All reported net benefits and loads resulting from net flows leaving the system of products that have not been assigned as co-products (there are none in this case) and have reached end-of-waste status are included in the Module D (reuse, recycling, direct energy recovery).\n\nProduction, trimming and end of life waste of Derbigum NT 4:\nAt end of life most of the product is recycled (patented process by Derbigum, and organised collection network).\n– A5, B4, C3: Installation and demolition waste: 95% is recycled in Derbigum facility.\n– The load for recycling is included (recycling unit is modelled with primary data)\n– Avoided material: The net flow of recycled material is calculated according to BE-PCR, and the corresponding amount of virgin bitumen is evaluated taking the efficiency of the recycling process into account.\n\nPallets: A5, B4: 0,2813 kg/FU; PCI = 12,24 MJ/kg\n– Reuse: 20%: 5,625 E-02 kg/FU; transport 20 km\n– Recycling (wood chips): 40% 0,1125 kg/FU; transport 20 km + chipping.\n– Incineration: 40%; 0,1125 kg/FU.\n\nEnergy recovery: efficiency\n– Pallet waste: incineration in a specific cogeneration unit, energy efficiency of 50% for thermal energy and 22% for electric energy.\n\nQUANTITATIVE DESCRIPTION OF THE LOADS BEYOND THE SYSTEM BOUNDARIES:\n– Recycling process for bituminous membrane waste\n– Transport for reused pallets: 20 km\n– Transport for recycled pallets: 20 km\n– Wood chipping of pallets\n\nQUANTITATIVE DESCRIPTION OF THE BENEFITS BEYOND THE SYSTEM BOUNDARIES:\n– Avoided virgin bitumen: 4,112 kg/FU\n– Pallet reused: 5,625 E-02 kg/FU\n– Wood chips (pallet recycled): 0,1125 kg/FU\n– Energy recovery:\no Heat: 0,6885 MJ/FU (substitution: thermal energy from natural gas)\no Electricity: 1,091 kWh/FU (or 0,3029 MJ/FU)(substitution: BE high voltage mix, excluding impact from the transmission network)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FBEPD_024.0156.002-01.00.00_Derbigum%2520NT%25204-%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/references",
      "@type": "Bibliography",
      "bibliography": [],
      "additionalInformation": [
        "Commercial names:\n– Derbigum NT 4 (4 mm thickness)\n– Derbigum NT 3 (3 mm thickness)\n– Roll: 1 m (width) x 8 m (length) = 8 m²\n– Pallet: 25 rolls (200 m²)",
        "Ratio between application and the reference flow in the EPD.\n– 1 (10,5% overlap included)\n– For different overlap: ratio (1+overlap)/(1+0,105)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FBEPD_024.0156.002-01.00.00_Derbigum%2520NT%25204-%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/sections",
      "@type": "EpdSectionSet",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "number": "11.1",
          "title": "Indoor air",
          "content": "This product does not come into contact with indoor air, so it has no impact on the health quality of indoor spaces."
        },
        {
          "number": "11.2",
          "title": "Soil and water",
          "content": "This product does not come into contact with indoor air, so it has no impact on the health quality of indoor spaces.\n\nThe product is not in contact withdrinking water but may be in contact with rainwater. No tests have been carried out."
        },
        {
          "number": "12",
          "title": "DEMONSTRATION OF VERIFICATION",
          "content": "The product is not in contact withdrinking water but may be in contact with rainwater. No tests have been carried out.\n\nVERIFICATION\n\nEN 15804+A2serves as the core PCR\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according tostandard EN ISO 14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier: Naeem Adibi,\n\nn.adibi@weloop.org\n\nWeLOOP S.A.R.L, http://weloop.org\n\nRue du Bourg 254, 59130 Lambersart–France"
        },
        {
          "number": "13",
          "title": "lca interpretation",
          "content": "11 RELEASE OF DANGEROUS\n\nSUBSTANCES TO INDOOR AIR,\n\nSOIL AND WATER DURING THE\n\nUSE STAG E\n\n11.1 Indoor air\n\nThis product does not come into contact with indoor air, so it has no impact on the health quality of indoor spaces.\n\n11.2 Soil and wate r\n\nThe product is not in contact withdrinking water but may be in contact with rainwater. No tests have been carried out.\n\n12 DEMONSTRATION OF\n\nVERIFICATION\n\nEN 15804+A2serves as the core PCR\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according tostandard EN ISO 14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier: Naeem Adibi,\n\nn.adibi@weloop.org\n\nWeLOOP S.A.R.L, http://weloop.org\n\nRue du Bourg 254, 59130 Lambersart–France\n\nThis study leads to the realisation of a B-EPD for the bitumen waterproofing products of Derbigum:Derbigum NT 4.\n\n.\n\nThe most impacted domain by theDerbigum NT 4is the Resource use, fossils, but this issue is partly compensated by the\n\nimportant recycling of the membrane at its end of life.\n\nThe main impacts of this product come from the sourcing and processing of raw materials (bitumen, polyester\n\nreinforcement, and polymers), and in a lesser extent to the manufacture of the products (consumption of natural gas for\n\nheat, and electricity).\n\nThe impactof the raw materialis \"doubled\" by the need of a replacement (i.e. addition of a new layer of Derbigum NT 4) on\n\nthe existing one) during the lifespan of the building to ensure a proper function.\n\nAlthough raw materials play a major role, their impact is limited, and the savings in virgin materials made by recycling\n\nmembranes and the use of recycled bitumen limit the impact of the process.\n\nOther ways of reducing environmental impact are to optimise energy consumption during manufacture and recycling, and\n\nto reduce the distance between the manufacturing and recycling sites (for example by duplicating the latter in a region closer\n\nto the target area).An extension of the RSL could also be an improvement.\n\nThe recycled content of theDerbigum NT 4represents 20,5% of the raw materials.\n\nDue to the implementation of a recycling chain to collect both installation trimming waste and demolition waste95% of the\n\nmembrane waste are recycled in the patented recycling process of Derbigum.\n\nThe production (A1-A3) of 1 FU ofDerbigum NT 4(1 m² installed, including an overlap of 10,5%) corresponds to the emission\n\nof3,92kg COeq/FU(3.in the Climate change category, and the consumption of182MJ for the Resource use, fossils.\n\n2\n\nThe total \"first life\" cycle (A1-A5) of 1 FU of Derbigum NT 4 (1 m² installed–fully torched, including an overlap of 10,5%)\n\ncorresponds to the emission of4,99kg CO2eq/FU in the Climate change category, and the consumption of 195 MJ for the\n\nResource use, fossils. Thereplacement (B4) after 40 years shows the same values as the A1 to A5 modules."
        },
        {
          "number": "16",
          "title": "ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON REVERSIBILITY",
          "content": "15 APPLICATION UNIT\n\nDerbigum NT is a bituminous waterproofing membraneCommercial names:\n\nmodified by plastomeric polymers. Derbigum NT partly– Derbigum NT 4(4mm thickness)\n\nconsists of bitumen extracted from recycled cutting waste– Derbigum NT3 (3 mm thickness)\n\nand used bituminous roofing membranes (Derbitumen). – Roll: 1 m (width) x 8 m (length) = 8 m²\n\nThe upper side of the Derbigum NT membrane is fitted with– Pallet:25rolls (200m²)\n\ntwo reinforcements , one glass-fibre and one non-woven – Ratio between application and the reference flow\n\npolyester (bothwith a recycled content). in the EPD.\n\n– 1 (10,5% overlap included)\n\nTheapplication unit is1m² installed(including 10,5% – For different overlap: ratio\n\noverlap necessary to ensure the full functionality). (1+overlap)/(1+0,105)\n\nApplications: .\n\n– Reinforced bituminous sheet for roof\n\nwaterproofing\n\n– Installation:fully torchedby use of flame,\n\nmechanical fixing,loose laying(under ballast),or\n\ncold bonded.\n\n– Specifically recommended when a high tearand\n\npuncture resistanceis required.\n\nInformation on scalability.The membrane is available in two\n\nthickness:4mm (Derbigum NT4) and 3 mm (Derbigum NT\n\n3).\n\nSince it isahomogeneous material, therescaling will be\n\nautomatically done in TOTEM, and the impacts will be\n\ncalculated for the selected thickness:ratio3/4=0,75.\n\nSimplicity of Ease of handling (sizeRobustness of material (material\n\nDescription Type of fixing Level of reversibility Speed of disassembly Comment\n\ndisassembly and weight) resistance to disassembly)\n\n– – –\n\nFlexible reinforcedWelded Non reversible connectionsSimple–requires the useSpeed of disassembly variesMaterial easy to manipulateDisassembly is possible but will likelyBitumenwaterproofing\n\nbitumenpolymer Fully torched of specific though commonfrom quick to slowby hand, one to two workerscause damage to the material due to themembrane\n\nmembranefor roof tools depending on elementrequired depending ontype of assembly or and tools usedand the\n\nwaterproofing: dimensions and number ofdimensions presence of additional layers\n\nfixations per distance unit\n\nFlexible reinforcedLoose laid Non reversible connectionsSimple–requires the useSpeed of disassembly variesMaterial easy to manipulateDisassembly is possible but will likelyBitumenwaterproofing\n\nbitumen polymer of specific though commonfrom quick to slowby hand, one to two workerscause damage to thematerial due to themembrane\n\nmembrane for roof tools depending on elementrequired depending ontype of assembly or and tools used and the\n\nwaterproofing: dimensions and number ofdimensions presence of additional layers\n\nfixations per distance unit\n\nFlexible reinforcedScrewed Non reversible connectionsSimple–requires the useSpeed of disassembly variesMaterial easy to manipulateDisassembly ispossible but will likelyBitumenwaterproofing\n\nbitumen polymer of specific though commonfrom quick to slowby hand, one to two workerscause damage to the material due to themembrane\n\nmembrane for roof tools depending on elementrequired depending ontype of assembly or and tools used and the\n\nwaterproofing: dimensions and number ofdimensions presence of additional layers\n\nfixations per distance unit\n\nFlexible reinforcedGlued Non reversible connectionsSimple–requires the useSpeed of disassembly variesMaterial easy to manipulateDisassembly is possible but will likelyBitumenwaterproofing\n\nbitumen polymer (Coldbonded) of specific though commonfrom quick to slowby hand, one to two workerscause damage to the material due to themembrane\n\nmembrane for roof tools depending on elementrequired depending ontype of assembly or and tools used and the\n\nwaterproofing: dimensions and number ofdimensions presence of additional layers\n\nfixations per distance unit"
        }
      ]
